= Foreword

I praise and thank Allāh, and I send blessings and peace upon Muḥammad, his
family, and his companions.

I read this booklet titled _Al-Tawḥīd al-muyassar_ prepared by Shaykh ʿAbdullāh
ibn Aḥmad al-Ḥuwayl, and found it to be a valuable resource. It contains the
definitions of Tawḥīd (monotheism) and _ʿibādah_ (worship), virtues of Tawḥīd,
examples of types of _ʿibādah_ that should only be directed to Allāh, and
mentions of some types of Shirk (associating others with Allāh) or what
diminishes the realization of true Tawḥīd. We recommend printing, publishing,
and distributing it in countries that have fallen into many types of Shirk due
to ignorance and blind following, hoping that Allāh the Exalted will benefit
those whom He wills good for.

And may peace and blessings be upon our prophet Muḥammad, his family and his
companions.

ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAbd al-Raḥmān al-Jibrīn \
